                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "### Most recent “What’s new today” story (Microsoft News)\n\n- **Title:** *How a single click fueled a global email scam*  \n- **Date:** Mar 4, 2026  \n- **Link:** https://blogs.microsoft.com/on-the-issues/2026/03/04/how-a-global-coalition-disrupted-tycoon/\n\n**Summary:**  \nMicrosoft reports on a large-scale email phishing operation tied to a service called **Tycoon 2FA**, which enabled attackers to steal credentials and **bypass multi-factor authentication**. The article explains how a single successful click can lead to account takeovers, operational disruption, and data theft at scale. It also details a **coordinated disruption effort** involving Microsoft, Europol, and other partners to take down the infrastructure supporting what they describe as one of the largest phishing operations on the internet.",
